TITLE: Implementing getStaticProps in Next.js
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of getStaticProps to fetch external data at build time for static page generation. Shows how to fetch blog posts and pass them as props to the page component.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextjsargentina/next.js-docs/blob/main/src/docs/03-pages/01-building-your-application/02-rendering/02-static-site-generation.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
export default function Blog({ posts }) {
  // Render posts...
}

// This function gets called at build time
export async function getStaticProps() {
  // Call an external API endpoint to get posts
  const res = await fetch('https://.../posts')
  const posts = await res.json()

  // By returning { props: { posts } }, the Blog component
  // will receive `posts` as a prop at build time
  return {
    props: {
      posts,
    },
  }
}
```

