TITLE: Updating Next.js Page for Draft Mode Data Fetching
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to update a Next.js page to fetch data based on the Draft Mode status. It uses the draftMode function to check if Draft Mode is enabled and fetches data from the appropriate URL.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextjsargentina/next.js-docs/blob/main/src/docs/02-app/01-building-your-application/07-configuring/11-draft-mode.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// page that fetches data
import { draftMode } from 'next/headers'

async function getData() {
  const { isEnabled } = draftMode()

  const url = isEnabled
    ? 'https://draft.example.com'
    : 'https://production.example.com'

  const res = await fetch(url)

  return res.json()
}

export default async function Page() {
  const { title, desc } = await getData()

  return (
    <main>
      <h1>{title}</h1>
      <p>{desc}</p>
    </main>
  )
}
```

