TITLE: Authentication-based Redirect using Next.js Middleware (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: JavaScript version of authentication-based redirects using Next.js Middleware. Redirects unauthenticated users to the login page when accessing protected routes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextjsargentina/next.js-docs/blob/main/src/docs/02-app/01-building-your-application/01-routing/06-redirecting.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { NextResponse } from 'next/server'
import { authenticate } from 'auth-provider'

export function middleware(request) {
  const isAuthenticated = authenticate(request)

  // If the user is authenticated, continue as normal
  if (isAuthenticated) {
    return NextResponse.next()
  }

  // Redirect to login page if not authenticated
  return NextResponse.redirect(new URL('/login', request.url))
}

export const config = {
  matcher: '/dashboard/:path*',
}
```

