TITLE: Creating a Client Component with Children Slot in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates creating a Client Component in TypeScript that accepts children as props. The component includes a button with a state counter and renders the children passed to it, creating a slot for Server Components.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextjsargentina/next.js-docs/blob/main/src/docs/02-app/01-building-your-application/03-rendering/03-composition-patterns.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
'use client'

import { useState } from 'react'

export default function ClientComponent({
  children,
}: {
  children: React.ReactNode
}) {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0)

  return (
    <>
      <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>{count}</button>
      {children}
    </>
  )
}
```

