TITLE: Creating Custom Spans with OpenTelemetry API in Next.js
DESCRIPTION: Example function that demonstrates how to create custom spans using the OpenTelemetry API. This function creates a 'fetchGithubStars' span to track a fetch request to GitHub.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextjsargentina/next.js-docs/blob/main/src/docs/02-app/01-building-your-application/06-optimizing/10-open-telemetry.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { trace } from '@opentelemetry/api'

export async function fetchGithubStars() {
  return await trace
    .getTracer('nextjs-example')
    .startActiveSpan('fetchGithubStars', async (span) => {
      try {
        return await getValue()
      } finally {
        span.end()
      }
    })
}
```

