TITLE: Adding Subtitles to Video Component in Next.js
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to enhance the video component by adding subtitle support using the HTML5 track element. The code fetches both video and subtitle files from Vercel Blob storage.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextjsargentina/next.js-docs/blob/main/src/docs/02-app/01-building-your-application/06-optimizing/02-videos.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
async function VideoComponent({ fileName }) {
  const {blobs} = await list({
    prefix: fileName,
    limit: 2
  });
  const { url } = blobs[0];
  const { url: captionsUrl } = blobs[1];

  return (
    <video controls preload="none" aria-label="Video player">
      <source src={url} type="video/mp4" />
      <track
        src={captionsUrl}
        kind="subtitles"
        srcLang="en"
        label="English">
      Your browser does not support the video tag.
    </video>
  );
};
```

