TITLE: Router Events Usage Example
DESCRIPTION: Example showing the correct way to handle router events using useEffect in Next.js 11.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextjsargentina/next.js-docs/blob/main/src/docs/03-pages/01-building-your-application/10-upgrading/08-version-11.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
useEffect(() => {
  const handleRouteChange = (url, { shallow }) => {
    console.log(
      `App is changing to ${url} ${
        shallow ? 'with' : 'without'
      } shallow routing`
    )
  }

  router.events.on('routeChangeStart', handleRouteChange)

  // If the component is unmounted, unsubscribe
  // from the event with the `off` method:
  return () => {
    router.events.off('routeChangeStart', handleRouteChange)
  }
}, [router])
```

