TITLE: Configuring Nginx Server for NextJS Static Export
DESCRIPTION: This Nginx configuration example shows how to set up a server to properly serve a NextJS static export. It includes route handling for the root directory and blog paths, along with 404 error handling.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nextjsargentina/next.js-docs/blob/main/src/docs/02-app/01-building-your-application/10-deploying/02-static-exports.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: nginx
CODE:
```
server {
  listen 80;
  server_name acme.com;

  root /var/www/out;

  location / {
      try_files $uri $uri.html $uri/ =404;
  }

  # This is necessary when `trailingSlash: false`.
  # You can omit this when `trailingSlash: true`.
  location /blog/ {
      rewrite ^/blog/(.*)$ /blog/$1.html break;
  }

  error_page 404 /404.html;
  location = /404.html {
      internal;
  }
}
```

